  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2936284601" />
    <a title="Nanette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3995288-nanette"><img alt="Nanette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613882438p2/3995288.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2936284601?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nanette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nanette" href="/user/show/3995288-nanette">Nanette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3995288-nanette?shelf=self-help">self-help</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3995288-nanette?shelf=mindfulness">mindfulness</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3995288-nanette?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3995288-nanette?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2936284601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8956187260675607166">So I enjoyed the first half of the book but began hearing an echo in the second half. Obviously the repetitive chants are mantras for meditation but it made for tedious reading. Definitely gonna apply a lot of what is here. Speaking of echoes, these thoughts are found throughout all religious disciplines and philosophies—they’re not new today nor were they new in 300 BC. What would be new is for the world to embrace the ideas and usher in peace—the Millennium. We can only try. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


